-- Siemens <SIEGn.DE> unveils overhaul, confirms Rolls-Royce buy
-- 
-- Tue May 06, 2014 04:33PM EDT
-- None



BERLIN, May 6 (Reuters) - German conglomerate Siemens <SIEGn.DE> announced a corporate overhaul on Tuesday which will streamline the structure of the company into nine divisions, see its healthcare business managed separately, and its audiology activities publicly listed.

In a statement, the Munich-based group also confirmed it was buying the energy business of Rolls-Royce <RR.L> for roughly 950 million euros.